Description: Ad [Addendum] Tower of Babel, R'dam: 1) L. Valkenborch: Tower of Babel, Munich, Pinakothek (1642). Based on van Beuningen. Typical V. Rocks; 2) L. Valckenborch, Also based on van Beuningen, but different composition in Koblenz M31, Text p. 21 with Nimrod. Attr. to L. Valckenborch plausible (rocks, typical); 3) with Nimrod, Louvre. Signed & dated 1594 based on R'dam picture; 4) Mainz, based on R'dam. Several more including a rectangular one rather far removed from Bruegel. For Tower of Babel see also M. van Valckenborch in Witt Library.
